# Arc: SailorArc | Scene: TheOldRoad4
# Source: C:\Program Files (x86)\Steam\steamapps\common\The Survival of Sarah Rose\game\script.rpy

translate ru strings:

    old "Sarah rose to the first light of daybreak."
    new "Sarah rose to the first light of daybreak."

    old "At first she had found it hard, but by now this was second nature."
    new "At first she had found it hard, but by now this was second nature."

    old "Wake. Prepare breakfast. Rig the cart. Back on the road."
    new "Wake. Prepare breakfast. Rig the cart. Back on the road."

    old "There was an efficiency to the whole process that she had come to appreciate."
    new "There was an efficiency to the whole process that she had come to appreciate."

    old "She even believed that she had begun to get the hang of the day-to-day workings of their convoy."
    new "She even believed that she had begun to get the hang of the day-to-day workings of their convoy."

    old "She didn't feel as though as was getting in the way of them as much as before, and she imagined they felt the same way."
    new "She didn't feel as though as was getting in the way of them as much as before, and she imagined they felt the same way."

    old "In no time at all, they were ready to get back out on the road."
    new "In no time at all, they were ready to get back out on the road."

    old "Sarah had taken the same place as always on the front box, and watched as Sigmund got up next to her."
    new "Sarah had taken the same place as always on the front box, and watched as Sigmund got up next to her."

    old "Sarah felt guilty about the night before."
    new "Sarah felt guilty about the night before."

    old "She had tricked him, or tried to at least, and he had done nothing to deserve such dishonesty from her."
    new "She had tricked him, or tried to at least, and he had done nothing to deserve such dishonesty from her."

    old "He almost barked his response."
    new "He almost barked his response."

    old "I wanted to apologize for what I did last night..."
    new "I wanted to apologize for what I did last night..."

    old "He grunted, but said nothing."
    new "He grunted, but said nothing."

    old "I kept bothering you about the bridge and your story and...I should have respected your privacy."
    new "I kept bothering you about the bridge and your story and...I should have respected your privacy."

    old "You should have."
    new "You should have."

    old "A heavy pause."
    new "A heavy pause."

    old "But...I'll accept your apology."
    new "But...I'll accept your apology."

    old "I don't like to share, but I should not have reacted as harshly as I did."
    new "I don't like to share, but I should not have reacted as harshly as I did."

    old "Sarah felt a weight fall from her shoulders, knowing Sigmund forgave her."
    new "Sarah felt a weight fall from her shoulders, knowing Sigmund forgave her."

    old "Thank you for forgiving me, and I promise I won't pry anymore."
    new "Thank you for forgiving me, and I promise I won't pry anymore."

    old "Now then, if we're done chatting about our feelings, how about we get back on the road?"
    new "Now then, if we're done chatting about our feelings, how about we get back on the road?"

    old "Let's go!"
    new "Let's go!"

    old "Sigmund snapped the reins and the cart pulled back onto the road."
    new "Sigmund snapped the reins and the cart pulled back onto the road."

    old "Almost a week went by, each day passing the same as the other."
    new "Almost a week went by, each day passing the same as the other."

    old "The only thing that seemed to change was the environment around them."
    new "The only thing that seemed to change was the environment around them."

    old "The trees slowly faded, growing sparser with each mile, where now instead an ocean of grass seemed to extend in every direction."
    new "The trees slowly faded, growing sparser with each mile, where now instead an ocean of grass seemed to extend in every direction."

    old "Sarah looked out each moment in awe at the sheer enormity of it all."
    new "Sarah looked out each moment in awe at the sheer enormity of it all."

    old "The tips of the blades of grass moved as the wind rushed across it, twisting and bending as it flowed through."
    new "The tips of the blades of grass moved as the wind rushed across it, twisting and bending as it flowed through."

    old "For the first time in her life, Sarah realized she could almost see the wind itself."
    new "For the first time in her life, Sarah realized she could almost see the wind itself."

    old "A nature like this could never have existed in her home country, she realized. Simply because the ever growing masses of people would seize on it eventually."
    new "A nature like this could never have existed in her home country, she realized. Simply because the ever growing masses of people would seize on it eventually."

    old "But out here, nature had won out over humanity, and it was humanity that was in retreat, and nature that advanced."
    new "But out here, nature had won out over humanity, and it was humanity that was in retreat, and nature that advanced."

    old "The others, for their part, seemed either long used to the sights or utterly uninterested."
    new "The others, for their part, seemed either long used to the sights or utterly uninterested."

    old "Still, Sarah was happy."
    new "Still, Sarah was happy."

    old "They had made good progress and she had seen few if any signs of bandits."
    new "They had made good progress and she had seen few if any signs of bandits."

    old "It was with good spirits that their wagon turned further along the road, coming upon the first sign of human life, outside of the old road itself, that Sarah had seen for days."
    new "It was with good spirits that their wagon turned further along the road, coming upon the first sign of human life, outside of the old road itself, that Sarah had seen for days."

    old "A small stone construct had been put up, blocking the road."
    new "A small stone construct had been put up, blocking the road."

    old "Beyond it, a small stone bridge extended from one side of the river bank to the other."
    new "Beyond it, a small stone bridge extended from one side of the river bank to the other."

    old "Sarah could hear Sigmund grunt, frustrated."
    new "Sarah could hear Sigmund grunt, frustrated."

    old "That ain't used to be there."
    new "That ain't used to be there."

    old "You mean the bridge?"
    new "You mean the bridge?"

    old "Nah, I mean that blockade in front of it."
    new "Nah, I mean that blockade in front of it."

    old "It didn't seem too difficult to get around to Sarah."
    new "It didn't seem too difficult to get around to Sarah."

    old "Can't we get past it?"
    new "Can't we get past it?"

    old "We can, but it ain't the obstacle that I worry about."
    new "We can, but it ain't the obstacle that I worry about."

    old "It's whatever group of fuckers decided to build it, and whatever reason they had I doubt it's any good."
    new "It's whatever group of fuckers decided to build it, and whatever reason they had I doubt it's any good."

    old "Sarah watched as Sigmund leaned back, his head dissapearing into the back of the cart."
    new "Sarah watched as Sigmund leaned back, his head dissapearing into the back of the cart."

    old "Sakar, Krip, gear up."
    new "Sakar, Krip, gear up."

    old "Sarah had seen plenty of squables in their group, mostly during the nights, but whenever out on the road, each seemed to yield to Sigmund."
    new "Sarah had seen plenty of squables in their group, mostly during the nights, but whenever out on the road, each seemed to yield to Sigmund."

    old "Despite whatever disagreement they might have, they all respected his leadership."
    new "Despite whatever disagreement they might have, they all respected his leadership."

    old "Sarah could hear the sound of weapons being drawn and readied."
    new "Sarah could hear the sound of weapons being drawn and readied."

    old "She could feel her heart begin to beat faster."
    new "She could feel her heart begin to beat faster."

    old "Out ahead, she still saw no signs of danger, but she sooner doubted her own instincts than those of the men she was travelling with."
    new "Out ahead, she still saw no signs of danger, but she sooner doubted her own instincts than those of the men she was travelling with."

    old "Finally, as their wagon turned the final bend in the road and pulled out ahead towards the construct, Sarah saw movement."
    new "Finally, as their wagon turned the final bend in the road and pulled out ahead towards the construct, Sarah saw movement."

    old "First, she saw two men moving atop the towers of the makeshift barricade."
    new "First, she saw two men moving atop the towers of the makeshift barricade."

    old "Then more still from the brush."
    new "Then more still from the brush."

    old "As their wagon continued to pull ahead, closer and closer, Sarah saw their numbers grow."
    new "As their wagon continued to pull ahead, closer and closer, Sarah saw their numbers grow."

    old "Turn around. That's what she wanted to tell Sigmund."
    new "Turn around. That's what she wanted to tell Sigmund."

    old "But she also knew there was nowhere for them to turn around to. The last vestige of civilization was more than a week behind them."
    new "But she also knew there was nowhere for them to turn around to. The last vestige of civilization was more than a week behind them."

    old "In total, Sarah counted some odd thirty people, gathered around the stone barricade."
    new "In total, Sarah counted some odd thirty people, gathered around the stone barricade."

    old "She had faith in her companions."
    new "She had faith in her companions."

    old "She had seen the damage that even Sigmund alone could inflict."
    new "She had seen the damage that even Sigmund alone could inflict."

    old "But this was something else. No matter how skilled they were, they could not defeat this many people."
    new "But this was something else. No matter how skilled they were, they could not defeat this many people."

    old "Sarah could feel her heart, by now pounding against her chest."
    new "Sarah could feel her heart, by now pounding against her chest."

    old "Finally, the wagon slowly rolled to a stop. Not too far from the men. Not too near."
    new "Finally, the wagon slowly rolled to a stop. Not too far from the men. Not too near."

    old "Sigmund seemed unfazed by the danger."
    new "Sigmund seemed unfazed by the danger."

    old "What's the meaning of this blockade?"
    new "What's the meaning of this blockade?"

    old "None spoke."
    new "None spoke."

    old "A single man from the crowd walked forward, coming up closer to the cart."
    new "A single man from the crowd walked forward, coming up closer to the cart."

    old "His posture seemed to suggest he was the one in charge."
    new "His posture seemed to suggest he was the one in charge."

    old "Captain\" \"This here bridge belongs to the Elyian Kingdom."
    new "Captain\" \"This here bridge belongs to the Elyian Kingdom."

    old "I've never heard of no fucking Elyian Kingdom and I don't quite imagine I care to learn."
    new "I've never heard of no fucking Elyian Kingdom and I don't quite imagine I care to learn."

    old "The captain didn't seem much fazed by Sigmund either."
    new "The captain didn't seem much fazed by Sigmund either."

    old "Captain\" \"The Elyian Kingdom was proclaimed five months ago by King Nathaniel Elyian, Lord of the northern hills, ruler of-"
    new "Captain\" \"The Elyian Kingdom was proclaimed five months ago by King Nathaniel Elyian, Lord of the northern hills, ruler of-"

    old "Sigmund interrupted the man."
    new "Sigmund interrupted the man."

    old "I don't give a rat's ass about who rules over this heap of rocks."
    new "I don't give a rat's ass about who rules over this heap of rocks."

    old "It was some other sorry bastard five months ago, and it will be another sorry bastard five months from now."
    new "It was some other sorry bastard five months ago, and it will be another sorry bastard five months from now."

    old "All I want is to get over this bridge and be on my way."
    new "All I want is to get over this bridge and be on my way."

    old "We don't mean no harm to you and yours, if you will just let us pass."
    new "We don't mean no harm to you and yours, if you will just let us pass."

    old "The captain eyed Sigmund, then the cart, and finally Sarah."
    new "The captain eyed Sigmund, then the cart, and finally Sarah."

    old "She could feel his eyes linger on her."
    new "She could feel his eyes linger on her."

    old "Captain\" \"Well, I suppose that puts us a bit at odds here."
    new "Captain\" \"Well, I suppose that puts us a bit at odds here."

    old "Captain\" \"Because you see, the king insists everyone who passes here pays a travel tax."
    new "Captain\" \"Because you see, the king insists everyone who passes here pays a travel tax."

    old "Sarah could see Sigmund shift in his seat. His blade was not far from his side."
    new "Sarah could see Sigmund shift in his seat. His blade was not far from his side."

    old "How much do you want?"
    new "How much do you want?"

    old "Captain\" \"What are you transporting, anyway?"
    new "Captain\" \"What are you transporting, anyway?"

    old "Is that any of your concern?"
    new "Is that any of your concern?"

    old "Sarah could see the man get frustrated."
    new "Sarah could see the man get frustrated."

    old "Captain\" \"Out here, whatever I want to be my concern, is my concern. So tell me what is in the wagon before I have my men turn it upside over."
    new "Captain\" \"Out here, whatever I want to be my concern, is my concern. So tell me what is in the wagon before I have my men turn it upside over."

    old "I wouldn't do that."
    new "I wouldn't do that."

    old "Captain\" \"Why not?"
    new "Captain\" \"Why not?"

    old "Because this wagon is loaded up with pyrrite. Enough of it to take out just about everyone and that bridge too."
    new "Because this wagon is loaded up with pyrrite. Enough of it to take out just about everyone and that bridge too."

    old "Sarah could see the man's face turn sour."
    new "Sarah could see the man's face turn sour."

    old "Sigmund reached back into the cart and pulled out a small shard of pyrrite. The ore glimmered in the sun, casting a yellowish hue."
    new "Sigmund reached back into the cart and pulled out a small shard of pyrrite. The ore glimmered in the sun, casting a yellowish hue."

    old "He tossed it at the man, who caught it."
    new "He tossed it at the man, who caught it."

    old "Passing the ore from hand to hand, and holding it up to the light, Sarah could see the captain was slowly becoming convinced."
    new "Passing the ore from hand to hand, and holding it up to the light, Sarah could see the captain was slowly becoming convinced."

    old "Captain\" \"It sure looks like pyrrite enough to me."
    new "Captain\" \"It sure looks like pyrrite enough to me."

    old "He turned back to face them."
    new "He turned back to face them."

    old "Captain\" \"Still, can't let you just pass by without paying a tax. Orders of the king and all."
    new "Captain\" \"Still, can't let you just pass by without paying a tax. Orders of the king and all."

    old "Tell me what you want."
    new "Tell me what you want."

    old "Captain\" \"Ten-thousand Lethram shillings."
    new "Captain\" \"Ten-thousand Lethram shillings."

    old "Even if I had that much on me, I wouldn't give it to you. Name a fair price or fuck off."
    new "Even if I had that much on me, I wouldn't give it to you. Name a fair price or fuck off."

    old "The captain was now getting visibly frustrated."
    new "The captain was now getting visibly frustrated."

    old "Captain\" \"Listen here you vagrant. This is my bridge, and these are my men. You want to get past it, you pay the tax."
    new "Captain\" \"Listen here you vagrant. This is my bridge, and these are my men. You want to get past it, you pay the tax."

    old "Best I can do for you is a hundred Lethram Shillings. Maybe a hundred Mythran Denars on top of that, but that's all the cash we can spare."
    new "Best I can do for you is a hundred Lethram Shillings. Maybe a hundred Mythran Denars on top of that, but that's all the cash we can spare."

    old "Now the captain laughed."
    new "Now the captain laughed."

    old "Captain\" \"That barely pays for me, let alone my men. How am I supposed to feed them if I let you and every other miserable son-of-a-bitch pass for a price like that?"
    new "Captain\" \"That barely pays for me, let alone my men. How am I supposed to feed them if I let you and every other miserable son-of-a-bitch pass for a price like that?"

    old "Is it my concern how you feed your men?"
    new "Is it my concern how you feed your men?"

    old "The man suddenly lowered his voice."
    new "The man suddenly lowered his voice."

    old "Captain\" \"Look, if I take that price, my men will think I'm weak."
    new "Captain\" \"Look, if I take that price, my men will think I'm weak."

    old "Captain\" \"I'd rather just let them kill you here than take that little money and lose my reputation."
    new "Captain\" \"I'd rather just let them kill you here than take that little money and lose my reputation."

    old "The captain gestured at Sarah."
    new "The captain gestured at Sarah."

    old "Captain\" \"How about the girl?"
    new "Captain\" \"How about the girl?"

    old "Captain\" \"You hand her over to us for an evening, I bet she can pay off whatever the tax is."
    new "Captain\" \"You hand her over to us for an evening, I bet she can pay off whatever the tax is."

    old "Give yourself over to the soldiers"
    new "Give yourself over to the soldiers"

    old "Hearing the captain's proposal, Sarah feels her cheeks turn red."
    new "Hearing the captain's proposal, Sarah feels her cheeks turn red."

    old "Still, from the corner of her eyes she can see Sigmund, and behind her she hears the others moving."
    new "Still, from the corner of her eyes she can see Sigmund, and behind her she hears the others moving."

    old "If she can keep them safe by giving herself up...wouldn't that be worth it?"
    new "If she can keep them safe by giving herself up...wouldn't that be worth it?"

    old "I...I accept!"
    new "I...I accept!"

    old "Sarah yells out the words as loudly as she can."
    new "Sarah yells out the words as loudly as she can."

    old "Sigmund turns to her, a stunned expression on his face."
    new "Sigmund turns to her, a stunned expression on his face."

    old "Sarah, you don't have to do this."
    new "Sarah, you don't have to do this."

    old "Sarah turns to Sigmund."
    new "Sarah turns to Sigmund."

    old "I know. I'm choosing to do this."
    new "I know. I'm choosing to do this."

    old "This will get us across the bridge, and it will keep you all safe..."
    new "This will get us across the bridge, and it will keep you all safe..."

    old "We're strong, Sarah, you don't have to protect us. We protect you..."
    new "We're strong, Sarah, you don't have to protect us. We protect you..."

    old "I know you're strong. But you're not thirty-men strong. Let me...let me do this, please."
    new "I know you're strong. But you're not thirty-men strong. Let me...let me do this, please."

    old "Sarah leaps down from the wagon before Sigmund can respond."
    new "Sarah leaps down from the wagon before Sigmund can respond."

    old "Walking up towards the captain, she can seem him grinning, perhaps he himself even surprised that she would agree."
    new "Walking up towards the captain, she can seem him grinning, perhaps he himself even surprised that she would agree."

    old "One night...that's it."
    new "One night...that's it."

    old "I spend one night here and then you let me and my friends pass, unharmed."
    new "I spend one night here and then you let me and my friends pass, unharmed."

    old "The captain nods."
    new "The captain nods."

    old "Captain\" \"You got my word on that, girly."
    new "Captain\" \"You got my word on that, girly."

    old "Sarah didn't know if his word was worth much at all, but she had little choice other than to trust him."
    new "Sarah didn't know if his word was worth much at all, but she had little choice other than to trust him."

    old "She felt the captain grab her wrist and begin to pull her away."
    new "She felt the captain grab her wrist and begin to pull her away."

    old "Looking back, Sarah quickly saw the wagon dissapear as they took her around a corner of the stone building."
    new "Looking back, Sarah quickly saw the wagon dissapear as they took her around a corner of the stone building."

    old "Off in the shadow of the building, there was a small makeshift camp. Some tents, a campfire, not a whole lot more than that."
    new "Off in the shadow of the building, there was a small makeshift camp. Some tents, a campfire, not a whole lot more than that."

    old "The man pushed her into one of the larger tents."
    new "The man pushed her into one of the larger tents."

    old "Captain\" \"How about you start by showing me what I just bought?"
    new "Captain\" \"How about you start by showing me what I just bought?"

    old "She had offered it to him, sure enough, but now the promise suddenly felt very real."
    new "She had offered it to him, sure enough, but now the promise suddenly felt very real."

    old "We agreed on one night...it's not night yet."
    new "We agreed on one night...it's not night yet."

    old "She saw the man roll his eyes."
    new "She saw the man roll his eyes."

    old "Captain\" \"It will be night soon."
    new "Captain\" \"It will be night soon."

    old "She faced him down."
    new "She faced him down."

    old "Soon isn't now."
    new "Soon isn't now."

    old "Captain\" \"Fine, I can be patient till nightfall."
    new "Captain\" \"Fine, I can be patient till nightfall."

    old "Captain\" \"But I'm gonna fuck this attitude right out of you."
    new "Captain\" \"But I'm gonna fuck this attitude right out of you."

    old "Sarah watched the man storm out of the tent before she could even respond."
    new "Sarah watched the man storm out of the tent before she could even respond."

    old "Sitting there alone, Sarah counted the hours passing as best she could manage from memory."
    new "Sitting there alone, Sarah counted the hours passing as best she could manage from memory."

    old "As time passed, Sarah could see the shadows grow longer, and the sounds outside the tent growing louder."
    new "As time passed, Sarah could see the shadows grow longer, and the sounds outside the tent growing louder."

    old "More and more soldiers were reporting back to the camp, no doubt leaving their posts after having learned of what their captain had secured for them."
    new "More and more soldiers were reporting back to the camp, no doubt leaving their posts after having learned of what their captain had secured for them."

    old "Knowing the time was close, Sarah began to undress herself."
    new "Knowing the time was close, Sarah began to undress herself."

    old "One by one, she dropped the pieces of her clothes off to the side, neatly folding them."
    new "One by one, she dropped the pieces of her clothes off to the side, neatly folding them."

    old "Sliding her hands past her body, she undid her underwear, leaving her entirely naked."
    new "Sliding her hands past her body, she undid her underwear, leaving her entirely naked."

    old "She instantly felt the cold night air moving over her body."
    new "She instantly felt the cold night air moving over her body."

    old "It was warmer here in the tent, but not by much."
    new "It was warmer here in the tent, but not by much."

    old "The sounds outside the tent grew rowdier in anticipation of the nights event."
    new "The sounds outside the tent grew rowdier in anticipation of the nights event."

    old "They were all here for her, Sarah realized."
    new "They were all here for her, Sarah realized."

    old "Had she made a mistake? No, Sarah steeled herself."
    new "Had she made a mistake? No, Sarah steeled herself."

    old "She had made this choice, for herself and her friends. She would see it through."
    new "She had made this choice, for herself and her friends. She would see it through."

    old "Suddenly, a bright light rushed into the tent."
    new "Suddenly, a bright light rushed into the tent."

    old "Before Sarah fully realized it, an explosion of sound and a blast of wind followed, scattering everything in the tent around."
    new "Before Sarah fully realized it, an explosion of sound and a blast of wind followed, scattering everything in the tent around."

    old "Sarah stumbled to the floor, her footing suddenly gone."
    new "Sarah stumbled to the floor, her footing suddenly gone."

    old "She tried to stable herself, but each time she tried to get up to her feet, she fell back down."
    new "She tried to stable herself, but each time she tried to get up to her feet, she fell back down."

    old "Around her, the rowdy cheers had been replaced by violent screams."
    new "Around her, the rowdy cheers had been replaced by violent screams."

    old "Something was happening."
    new "Something was happening."

    old "But Sarah struggled to know what."
    new "But Sarah struggled to know what."

    old "Were they attacked? Was she in danger? Had this all been for nothing?"
    new "Were they attacked? Was she in danger? Had this all been for nothing?"

    old "Just as she raised up her head towards the entrance, a man came rushing in."
    new "Just as she raised up her head towards the entrance, a man came rushing in."

    old "Sarah, come with me."
    new "Sarah, come with me."

    old "He extended his hand to her, and she eagerly grabbed it."
    new "He extended his hand to her, and she eagerly grabbed it."

    old "As he pulled her out and away from the tent, Sarah saw the carnage that had come upon the camp."
    new "As he pulled her out and away from the tent, Sarah saw the carnage that had come upon the camp."

    old "All around the camp, soldiers were crawling across the ground, blood streaming from their bodies."
    new "All around the camp, soldiers were crawling across the ground, blood streaming from their bodies."

    old "Fires seemed to rage everywhere, turning the night bright."
    new "Fires seemed to rage everywhere, turning the night bright."

    old "She barely had time to consider any of it, Sakar kept pulling her along, not giving her a moment to pause."
    new "She barely had time to consider any of it, Sakar kept pulling her along, not giving her a moment to pause."

    old "Don't linger!"
    new "Don't linger!"

    old "Sarah slowly awoke back to herself."
    new "Sarah slowly awoke back to herself."

    old "With each step, she found her footing, beginning to run along side of Sakar rather than just being dragged by him."
    new "With each step, she found her footing, beginning to run along side of Sakar rather than just being dragged by him."

    old "She long forgot her own nakedness as they together ran back to the wagon."
    new "She long forgot her own nakedness as they together ran back to the wagon."

    old "Sigmund and Krip stood there, already waiting."
    new "Sigmund and Krip stood there, already waiting."

    old "Several bodies, no longer moving, were scattered around the cart."
    new "Several bodies, no longer moving, were scattered around the cart."

    old "Blood dripped from their weapons."
    new "Blood dripped from their weapons."

    old "Here, put these on when you're on the cart!"
    new "Here, put these on when you're on the cart!"

    old "Sarah felt Sakar shoving her own clothes into her hands. He must have grabbed them in the confusion."
    new "Sarah felt Sakar shoving her own clothes into her hands. He must have grabbed them in the confusion."

    old "Sarah climbed onto the box of the cart and began to get dressed as best she could."
    new "Sarah climbed onto the box of the cart and began to get dressed as best she could."

    old "Next to her, she saw Sigmund jump onto the wagon and forcing the horses into motion."
    new "Next to her, she saw Sigmund jump onto the wagon and forcing the horses into motion."

    old "Ahead, the road now seemed clear for them, the barricade now a smoldering ruin."
    new "Ahead, the road now seemed clear for them, the barricade now a smoldering ruin."

    old "Screams still rang out across the night."
    new "Screams still rang out across the night."

    old "But it didn't matter. The cart rushed forward and before she knew it, they had passed over the small bridge and were clear on the other side."
    new "But it didn't matter. The cart rushed forward and before she knew it, they had passed over the small bridge and were clear on the other side."

    old "Behind them, the screams quickly faded into the night, as did the light of the fires."
    new "Behind them, the screams quickly faded into the night, as did the light of the fires."

    old "Just as she concluded her decision, Sarah saw the opening of the tent pulled back."
    new "Just as she concluded her decision, Sarah saw the opening of the tent pulled back."

    old "The captain walked back into the tent."
    new "The captain walked back into the tent."

    old "Captain\" \"Well, girly, last rays of sun just vanished behind the horizon. Time to pay up."
    new "Captain\" \"Well, girly, last rays of sun just vanished behind the horizon. Time to pay up."

    old "She saw him realize that she was already naked, his eyes going wide as they roamed across her body."
    new "She saw him realize that she was already naked, his eyes going wide as they roamed across her body."

    old "I'm...ready..."
    new "I'm...ready..."

    old "Sarah turned her eyes low."
    new "Sarah turned her eyes low."

